    "attributes": {
        "action": "Certify & Remove VAT on bee-friendly plants to support pollinator conservation",
        "additional_details": "Pollinators are in crisis \u2014 with some studies warning of up to 50% species loss by 2050. In the UK, pollinator populations continue to decline due to pesticide use, habitat loss, and climate change.\r\n \r\nWe think many citizens want to help, but barriers remain. We believe that removing VAT from nectar- and pollen-rich plants would:\r\n\u2022 Encourage people to grow pollinator-friendly gardens\r\n\u2022 Support the UK\u2019s Healthy Bees Plan 2030\r\n\u2022 Align taxation with sustainability goals\r\n\u2022 Empower households and communities to act\r\n\r\nWe think this small fiscal adjustment could lead to meaningful change for biodiversity, public engagement, and food security.\r\nPlease support a 0% VAT rate for bee-friendly plants.",
        "background": "We call on the UK Government to certify and remove VAT from bee-friendly plants and seeds.",
